This paper is likely to belong to the Neural Networks and Deep Learning (cs.NE) category as it focuses on improving the memory component of Neural Turing Machines, which are a type of neural network. It could also be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes new structures for the memory component to improve learning. Additionally, it involves Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it aims to improve the performance of a machine learning model. The paper also mentions tasks related to natural language processing (associative recall task) and computer vision (copy task), which could place it under the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), respectively.
